description.narrative:
The overall objective of the Review is to assess the 92 Group’s performance in delivering results in relation to its engagement with the MFA (DED) and assess the extent to which the 92 Group is relevant and adds value to its members in relation to the overall framework of the Danish strategy for development cooperation and humanitarian action – The World 2030 and The Government’s Priorities for Danish Development Cooperation 2019.

Specifically, the Review should assess the 92 Group’s approach, capacity and performance with a view to assess: 
1) How the 92 Group as a network adds value to its members especially in relation to sustaining social, economic and environmental change in the developing countries;
2) How the 92 Group performs according to the mandate as a network organisation, working towards strengthening Danish civil society in terms of influencing national and international fora, discussions, and decisions on sustainable development in developing countries, specifically within the areas of Sustanable Development Goals, Climate and energy, and Corporate Social Responsibility;
3) The cooperation and relation with other actors, including related networks of similar character. 

The Review should issue recommendations, which should provide an input to the MFA’s ongoing dialogue with the 92 Group.
